'''Nan Talese''' (n<U+00E9>e Ahern) is an [[United States|American]] editor and a veteran of the [[New York]] publishing industry. She is the wife of the writer [[Gay Talese]]. They have two daughters: Pamela (a painter), and Catherine (a photographer).
According to http://www.randomhouse.com/nanatalese/about.html, Talese is Senior Vice President of Doubleday and the Publisher and Editorial Director of Nan A. Talese/Doubleday. At [[Random House]] and earlier at [[Simon & Schuster]] and [[Houghton Mifflin]], she has had 'editorial relationships' with [[Pat Conroy]], [[Margaret Atwood]], [[Ian McEwan]], [[Barry Unsworth]] and [[Thomas Keneally]]. Less happily, perhaps, her imprint also published [[James Frey]]'s discredited memoir "A Million Little Pieces".

